#: ../../../vtk_file_formats/vtkhdf_file_format/vtkhdf_specifications.md:1
msgid "VTKHDF format specification"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vtk_file_formats/vtkhdf_file_format/vtkhdf_specifications.md:3
msgid "General Specification"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vtk_file_formats/vtkhdf_file_format/vtkhdf_specifications.md:5
msgid ""
"VTKHDF files start with a group called `VTKHDF` with two attributes: "
"`Version` and `Type`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vtk_file_formats/vtkhdf_file_format/vtkhdf_specifications.md:8
msgid ""
"Top-level groups outside of `/VTKHDF` do not contain any information related "
"to VTK data model and are outside of the scope of this specification. They "
"can be useful to store meta-information that could be read and written by "
"custom VTKHDF implementations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vtk_file_formats/vtkhdf_file_format/vtkhdf_specifications.md:14
msgid ""
"Unless specified otherwise, every mention of \"dataset\" in this doc refers "
"to a [HDF5 dataset](https://support.hdfgroup.org/documentation/hdf5/latest/"
"_h5_d__u_g.html) and not a VTK dataset."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vtk_file_formats/vtkhdf_file_format/vtkhdf_specifications.md:17
msgid "Versioning"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vtk_file_formats/vtkhdf_file_format/vtkhdf_specifications.md:19
msgid ""
"VTKHDF File format stores the version in the related attribute `Version`. It "
"is an array of 2 integers `[X,Y]` where `X` is the major and `Y` the minor. "
"Major version will be updated for any API break. Minor version will be "
"updated when any new specification is made."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vtk_file_formats/vtkhdf_file_format/vtkhdf_specifications.md:23
msgid ""
"It ensures that any file will be read/write correctly for any different "
"minor version in the same major by an implementation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vtk_file_formats/vtkhdf_file_format/vtkhdf_specifications.md:25
msgid ""
"See the [changelog](vtkhdf_introduction.md#changelog) to be up-to-date "
"regarding any addition or API break."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vtk_file_formats/vtkhdf_file_format/vtkhdf_specifications.md:27
msgid "Type"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vtk_file_formats/vtkhdf_file_format/vtkhdf_specifications.md:29
msgid ""
"The attribute `Type` is a string showing the VTK dataset type stored in the "
"file. It can be : `ImageData`, `PolyData`, `UnstructuredGrid`, "
"`HyperTreeGrid`, `OverlappingAMR`,  `PartitionedDataSetCollection` or "
"`MultiBlockDataSet`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vtk_file_formats/vtkhdf_file_format/vtkhdf_specifications.md:33
msgid "Dataset type"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vtk_file_formats/vtkhdf_file_format/vtkhdf_specifications.md:35
msgid ""
"The data type for each HDF dataset is part of the dataset and it is "
"determined at write time. The reader matches the type of the dataset with a "
"`H5T_NATIVE_` type and creates the VTK array of that type. Consequently, the "
"type at writing might be different than the type at reading even on the same "
"machine because for instance `long` can be the same type as `long long` or "
"`int` can be the same as `long` on certain platforms. Also, `vtkIdType` is "
"read as the C++ type it represents (`long` or `long long`). Endianness "
"conversions are done automatically."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vtk_file_formats/vtkhdf_file_format/vtkhdf_specifications.md:45
msgid ""
"In the diagrams that follow, showing the HDF file structure for VTK "
"datasets, the rounded blue rectangles are HDF groups. Gray rectangles are "
"HDF datasets and purple rectangle is for symbolic link. Each rectangle shows "
"the name of the group or dataset and the `Attributes` underneath :"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vtk_file_formats/vtkhdf_file_format/vtkhdf_specifications.md:64
msgid "Attribute Data"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vtk_file_formats/vtkhdf_file_format/vtkhdf_specifications.md:66
msgid ""
"Attribute data (point, cell, field) is stored in HDF5 datasets located in "
"the `VTKHDF/[Point/Cell/Field]Data` groups."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vtk_file_formats/vtkhdf_file_format/vtkhdf_specifications.md:69
msgid ""
"Each point and cell array can define the \"Attribute\" HDF5 attribute to "
"mark the array as carrying a special meaning, corresponding to types defined "
"in `vtkDataSetAttributes`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../vtk_file_formats/vtkhdf_file_format/vtkhdf_specifications.md:72
msgid "Possible values for \"Attribute\" are (case-insensitive):"
msgstr ""

